cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of monocular 3D human-pose estimation from static images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a Deep Conditional Variational Autoencoder based model, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also proposes two strategies for obtaining the final 3D pose, which involves ranking and scoring, making it likely to fall under cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the paper reports results on benchmark datasets, indicating that it involves experiments and evaluations, making it likely to fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
